Ansible Installation
















Master Configuration(ubuntu)

1.http://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/installation_guide/intro_installation.html#control-machine-requirements
2. Check for Python by typing python
 










3. Create User <ansible>

 

4.Give sudo privilages to the user ansible

 

 

5. Set Password authentication to “yes”
 

 

6. Service ssh restart

 


Node 1(Ubuntu)
1.	Check for python (python is the only prereq for node)
2.	Create User <ansible>
 

3.Give SUDO previlages to ansible

 

 












4.Change password authentication to “yes”( vi /etc/ssh/sshd_config)

 


 








	SSh-keygen (In Master user ansible)

 



 

 


Node 2
1.	Check for python 

2.	Adduser ansible
 

3.	Add ansible to sudo group
 

 
4.	Change password authentication to “yes”

 

 


5.	Restart SSH(service ssh restart)



Master(ansible User)

 
 ssh ansible@privateDNS

 


